 i. sin^{-1}x + sin^{-1}y = sin^{-1} \{x\sqrt{1 - y^{2}} + y\sqrt{1 - x^{2}}\}
 where -1 \leq x, y \leq 1 and x^{2} + y^{2} \leq 1
 ii. cos^{-1}x + cos^{-1}y = cos^{-1} \{xy - \sqrt{(1-x^{2})(1-y^{2})}\}
 where -1 \leq x, y \leq 1 and x + y \geq 1
 iii. tan^{-1}x + tan^{-1}y = tan^{-1} \frac{x + y}{1 - xy}
 where x > 0, y > 0 and 0 \leq xy \leq 1
 Which one is correct?

